{{!--
  Custom .desktop template for Linux bundles, referenced from
  tauri.linux.conf.json (bundle.linux.deb.desktopTemplate).

  On Linux, Tauri derives the package name (deb/rpm) from `productName`, with
  no way to set the two independently (https://github.com/tauri-apps/tauri/issues/13999,
  still open). We override `productName` to "radicle-desktop" in
  tauri.linux.conf.json so the package and its artifacts are named
  "radicle-desktop" (the Arch PKGBUILD also globs on that name). The cost is
  that the launcher/menu entry would otherwise read "radicle-desktop" too.

  This template is Tauri's built-in default with a single change: `Name` is
  hardcoded to "Radicle" instead of `{{name}}`, so the app shows as "Radicle"
  in the desktop environment while the package stays "radicle-desktop". Keep
  every other line in sync with Tauri's default template on major upgrades.
--}}
[Desktop Entry]
Categories={{categories}}
{{#if comment}}
Comment={{comment}}
{{/if}}
Exec={{exec}}
Icon={{icon}}
Name=Radicle
Terminal=false
Type=Application
